  "prompt": "If a friend has body odor, should I tell her?",
  "response": "This can be a sensitive situation. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Be kind and discreet\n- Choose a private moment\n- Speak gently and compassionately\n- Focus on concern for her, not embarrassment\n\n2. How to approach the conversation\n- Use \"I\" statements like \"I've noticed...\"\n- Avoid harsh language or judgment\n- Offer support if there might be an underlying health issue\n\n3. Possible reasons for body odor\n- Medical conditions\n- Hygiene habits\n- Diet\n- Medication side effects\n\n4. Potential approaches\n- Ask if everything is okay health-wise\n- Suggest seeing a doctor if you're concerned\n- Offer to help if she seems unaware\n\n5. What to avoid\n- Public confrontation\n- Mocking or teasing\n- Telling other people\n\nThe goal is to help your friend while preserving her dignity and your friendship.",
